(1) What is monit and mmonit?

Monit :-
	It is an Open source utility used for managing and monitoring unix/linux systems. Monit conducts automatic maintenance and repair and executes meaningful casual actions in error situations.

M/Monit :-
	M/Monit uses Monit as an agent and will manage and monitor all our hosts and services. It has a clean, simple and well designed user interface. 


(2) How monit communicate with mmonit?
	To setup communication between monit and mmonit add the below statements on to the monit control file.

# vi /etc/monit/monitrc
#General Format
```
set mmonit http://<user>:<password>@<M/Monit-host>:<port>/collector

set httpd port 2812 and use address <monit-host>

allow localhost

allow <M/Monit-host>

allow username:password
```

